race.description: Country Comfort Perth - Racy Weekend Getaway Mdn
race.comment: HELLAVAMOMENT (7) looked sharp at the trial and followed a 1.3L defeat here on debut with a placed effort at Northam when he finished well after settling too far back. Strips fitter and has the winkers on for the first time. Has a low gate and is ready to win. LEMMOR (5) resumed here in solid order and then ran a big number narrowly beaten at Ascot is tougher grade. Surprised the market, but he'll be right in this if he holds that form. BUBBLES IN RIO (4) is free running and third up should be ready to find this best. That form would give him winning claims. ACORN (2) debuted in a strong form race at Northam but raced erratically. She just missed in a Lark Hill trial since and will have taken fitness and learning. Draws wide but Pike is a key jockey switch and a much better effort is likely.
